{{Quote|The only intact set of records is here on Bastion, and I've already dealt with them.''"''<br />''"''Actually, that's not entirely accurate. The records at the Ubiqtorate base on Yaga Minor may also contain a copy.|Vilim Disra and Grodin Tierce|<ref name="SotP">''[[Specter of the Past]]''</ref>}}
The '''Ubiqtorate base''' orbiting [[Yaga Minor/Legends|Yaga Minor]] was an archive of information for the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], and later the [[Imperial Remnant]], under the command of [[High General]] [[Hestiv]].<ref name="SotP" />

In [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]], it was targeted by [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[General/Legends|General]] [[Garm Bel Iblis/Legends|Garm Bel Iblis]], who led a raid on the station to secure a copy of the [[Caamas Document]]. While the [[Battle of Yaga Minor (Galactic Civil War)|Battle of Yaga Minor]] did not lead to an unaltered copy of the document being recovered by the New Republic, the intervention of [[Talon Karrde]] and [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gilad Pellaeon/Legends|Gilad Pellaeon]] at the end of the battle exposed the three conspirators ([[Major/Legends|Major]] [[Grodin Tierce]], [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] [[Vilim Disra]], and the con-artist [[Flim (Human)|Flim]]) who had seized power in the Imperial Remnant in order to enrich themselves and prolong the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. The battle, along with a [[Battle of Bothawui (Galactic Civil War)|battle at Bothawui]], thus marked the end of the war.

